snoopy.blindnote: sno/scaRNAs with same target 18S rRNA U1692 : SNORA70 SNORA70B SNORA70C SNORA70D SNORA70E SNORA70F SNORA70G. 2009年6月18日（山元）snoRNABaseより。Homo sapiens U70F snoRNA. This H/ACA box snoRNA was described by Weber (2006) as a primate-specific U70 Type 3 snoRT, and was also identified by Luo and Li (2007). It is present in human, chimp, orangutan, rhesus and marmoset genomes. Twelve human U70 type 3 snoRTs reside in an intron of a known gene in the sense orientation, including U70B (USP34), U70C (ASTN2), U70D (PHLPPL), U70E (RAB30), U70F (COBLL1) and U70G (RAP1B) (Weber, 2006; Luo and Li, 2007).
